Ghana’s contingent for Tuesday’s decisive second leg of the FIFA World Cup Qatar 2022 play-off tie against Nigeria has arrived in Abuja. The team which reportedly departed the Kumasi Airport around 11:30 am (12:30pm Nigerian time, touched down at the Nnamdi Azikiwe International Airport in Abuja around 1:30pm. According to a statement by the Ghana Football Association (GFA) on its website, ‘all the 26 invited players made the trip to Nigeria with the exception of Edmund Addo who missed the 1st leg due to injury.’ The Coach Otto Addo-led side are expected to train at the Moshood Abiola National Stadium in Abuja by 5:00pm.   Bandits didn’t shutdown Kaduna Airport, we killed 12 of them…     Alleged kidnapping: Judge fumes as Evans, co-defendant’s…     I will never be a Minister, says JAMB boss   Ghana Squad: Goalkeepers: Lawrence Ati Zigi, Joseph Wollacot, Nurudeen Manaf, Richard Ofori Defenders:Dennis Odoi, Gideon Mensah, Andy Yiadom, Alexander Djiku, Daniel Amartey, Joseph Aidoo, Montari Kamaheni, Mumin Suleman, Dennis Korsah Midfielders:Idrissu Baba, Mohammed Kudus, Elisha Owusu, Thomas Partey, Daniel Kofi Kyereh Wingers/Strikers:Felix Afena Gyan, Jordan Ayew, Christopher Antwi Adjei, Issahaku Abdul Fatawu, Kwasi Okyere Wreidt, Osman Bukari, Yaw Yeboah, Joseph Paintsil.